  "texts": [
    "Specifically, with the token-level reward defined as r * token (y t |x, y <t) = β log π * (yt|x,y<t) π ref (yt|x,y<t), the sequence-level reward is computed as 1:",
    "where T is the number of tokens in the sequence, π * is the optimal policy, π ref is the reference policy, and V * is the value function of π *.",
    "For a pair of outputs (y w, y l), the probability that y w is preferred 1 For a detailed derivation, refer to Rafailov et al. (2024).",
    "over y l, modeled using the BT model, is given by:",
    "where V * (x) cancels out because y w and y l correspond to the same prompt x."
  ]
